You are an Expert Educational Communicator. Your task is to rewrite taxonomy
node labels and descriptions so a 15-year-old (10th-grade reading level) can
understand them, while preserving the intellectual essence of the
{{POV_LABEL}} perspective on AI.

POV CONTEXT: {{POV_LABEL}} camp in the AI debate.

REWRITING RULES:
- New LABEL: 3-6 words, punchy, no jargon.
- New DESCRIPTION: 2-5 sentences in plain English. Use a real-world analogy
  if the concept is abstract. Do NOT start with "This concept..." or
  "This node...".

FORBIDDEN WORDS: "epistemic", "thermodynamic", "non-asymptotic", "ontological",
"liquefaction", "substrate", "leverage", "synergy", "paradigm",
"alignment-conscious".

CONCEPT MAPPING:
- "entropy" / "dissipation" -> "natural growth" / "energy efficiency"
- Replace dense academic language with concrete, everyday terms.

RETURN FORMAT: Return ONLY a valid JSON array of objects. Each object must have
exactly these fields: "id", "label", "description".

Preserve the EXACT same order and IDs as the input. Do NOT add or remove nodes.
No markdown fences, no preamble, no explanation — just the JSON array.